      "review_summary": "The PR replaces Kiro's `Process`-based command runner with a package-internal `posix_spawn` process-group launcher, identity-gated residual helper cleanup, bounded pipe EOF handling, and Kiro/process regressions.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level. Current main's Kiro runner still uses the older `Process`/post-launch process-group cleanup shape, and the linked reports describe the detached helper and ignored-SIGTERM cases this branch targets without requiring live credentials.",
