      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: clean up Kiro CLI helper processes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- launch Kiro CLI commands in a dedicated process group established before `exec`\n- bound process termination and output draining when descendants retain inherited pipes\n- discover escaped pipe holders and same-group helpers by start-time-verified identities\n- keep the exited root unreaped during residual cleanup so its PID/process-group ID cannot be reused\n- refresh same-group identities after `TERM`, covering helpers forked during cleanup\n- close unrelated inherited descriptors on Linux, matching the macOS close-on-exec contract\n- preserve existing timeout, cancellation, output, and exit-status behavior\n\nFollow-up to https://github.com/steipete/CodexBar/issues/1533 and https://github.com/steipete/CodexBar/issues/1535.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe original Kiro runner could wait indefinitely after termination or parent exit: `waitUntilExit()` had no `KILL` escalation, and final EOF reads remained blocked while descendants retained inherited output pipes.\n\nThe bounded repair establishes a process group before `exec`, records exact output-pipe holders, and keeps the exited root unreaped while residual identities are collected and terminated. The exit waiter uses portable blocking `waitid(WEXITED | WNOWAIT)`, then reaps only after cleanup requests completion. Signals target only start-time-verified identities, including group members discovered after `TERM`; Linux launch also closes unrelated parent descriptors.\n\n## Proof\n\nExact head: `0a3493db1f8afcb84dff1a0504c016a634dbc131`\n\n- focused Kiro/process tests: 43 passed, including inherited-descriptor isolation and a helper that forks during post-root-exit `SIGTERM` cleanup\n- `make test`: 470 deterministic selections across 40 shards passed\n- `make check`: parser/package/release guards passed; SwiftFormat clean; SwiftLint 0 violations across 1117 files\n- `git diff --check`: passed\n- exact branch autoreview: clean; no accepted or actionable findings\n- release `CodexBarCLI` SHA-256: `3b7c6c8c72c80787a7249d9b21952ea1665be61ce5c5618997e9853e24c71195`\n- isolated release CLI proof, synthetic account only:\n  - normal parent exit with inherited pipe: 0.998s, parsed usage, child removed, heartbeat stopped, empty stderr\n  - idle timeout with parent and child ignoring `TERM`: 10.955s, parsed usage, child removed, heartbeat stopped, empty stderr\n  - root exited before residual helper forked during `TERM`: 0.601s, parsed usage, child removed, heartbeat stopped, empty stderr\n\nNo live credentials, browser data, or Keychain access were used.\n\n## Risk\n\nThe new launcher is package-internal and currently used only by Kiro. Darwin process-group enumeration uses `proc_listpids`; Linux filters `/proc`. Every terminating signal is gated by a stable process start identity. The root is retained as an unreaped child only during bounded cleanup, with a 30-second defensive auto-reap if the owner fails to finish.\n",
        "branch": "fix/1533-kiro-descendant-cleanup",
